name: hdc_streaming_inference
version: "1.0.0"
language: zig
module: hdc_streaming_inference

description: |
  HDC Streaming Inference — Level 10A.1.1: Real-Time Token Generation.
  Autoregressive generation loop with KV-cache, phi-rank decoding,
  and token-by-token output for interactive chat.

  === STREAMING ARCHITECTURE ===
  Standard LLM streaming: generate one token, yield, append, repeat.
  HDC streaming: same pattern but all ops are ternary bind/bundle.

  Loop:
    1. Encode context tokens via codebook (cached after first pass)
    2. Forward pass through L transformer blocks
    3. Decode output HV at last position → next token
    4. Yield token to caller (streaming callback)
    5. Append token to context, shift window if > context_length
    6. Repeat until EOS or max_length

  === KV-CACHE (HDC-NATIVE) ===
  Standard KV-cache stores float K and V matrices per layer.
  HDC KV-cache stores trit vectors (5 trits/byte):
    cache[layer][head][position] = (K_hv, V_hv)  -- 2 * D trits per entry
  Memory for D=256, n=512, H=3, L=2:
    2 * 256 * 512 * 3 * 2 = 1,572,864 trits = ~314KB packed
  vs float32 KV-cache: 2 * 256 * 512 * 3 * 2 * 4 = 6.3MB
  Savings: ~20x memory reduction.

  Cache update: only compute K,V for new token (incremental bind).
  Attention: reuse cached K,V for all previous positions.
  Invalidation: slide window, evict oldest entries.

  === DECODING STRATEGIES ===
  1. Greedy: argmax(similarity(output_hv, codebook))
  2. Phi-Rank Sampling: weight candidates by phi^(-rank/T), sample
  3. Top-K: restrict to K most similar, sample uniformly
  4. Nucleus (Top-P): accumulate phi-weights until sum > P, sample from set
  5. Repetition Penalty: reduce similarity for recently generated tokens

  === STOP CONDITIONS ===
  - EOS token detected (codebook.decode returns "<eos>")
  - max_length reached
  - Confidence below threshold (similarity < 0.1 = model is lost)
  - Repetition loop detected (same 3+ tokens repeated)

  === PERFORMANCE (D=256, L=2, H=3) ===
  First token (full context): ~3.7ms (16 tokens * 2 blocks * 115us)
  Subsequent tokens (with KV-cache): ~0.23ms (1 token * 2 blocks * 115us)
  Streaming throughput: ~4,300 tokens/sec
  Time to first token: 3.7ms (interactive-grade)

  Trinity Identity: phi^2 + 1/phi^2 = 3
  Sacred Formula: V = n * 3^k * pi^m * phi^p * e^q

types:
  StreamConfig:
    fields:
      max_length: usize
      temperature: Float
      top_k: usize
      top_p: Float
      repetition_penalty: Float
      stop_tokens: List<String>
      min_confidence: Float
      use_kv_cache: Bool

  KVCacheEntry:
    fields:
      position: usize
      key_hv: List<i8>
      value_hv: List<i8>

  KVCache:
    fields:
      entries: List<List<List<KVCacheEntry>>>
      num_layers: usize
      num_heads: usize
      max_positions: usize
      current_length: usize

  StreamToken:
    fields:
      token: String
      confidence: Float
      position: usize
      elapsed_ns: u64

  StreamState:
    fields:
      context: List<String>
      generated: List<StreamToken>
      kv_cache: KVCache
      total_tokens: usize
      is_finished: Bool
      stop_reason: String

  StreamStats:
    fields:
      tokens_generated: usize
      time_to_first_token_ms: Float
      avg_token_latency_ms: Float
      peak_memory_bytes: u64
      cache_hit_rate: Float
      avg_confidence: Float

  HDCStreamingEngine:
    fields:
      allocator: Allocator
      config: StreamConfig
      engine: HDCForwardEngine
      state: StreamState
      recent_tokens: List<String>

behaviors:
  - name: initStreaming
    given: StreamConfig and HDCForwardEngine reference
    when: Initializes KV-cache, sets decoding params, clears state
    then: Streaming engine ready for generation

  - name: initKVCache
    given: Number of layers, heads, max positions, dimension
    when: Allocates cache entries as packed trit arrays
    then: Empty KV-cache ready for incremental fill

  - name: encodeNewToken
    given: Token string and position
    when: Encodes via codebook, computes K and V projections for all heads/layers
    then: Returns K,V hypervectors and updates KV-cache

  - name: forwardWithCache
    given: New token position and existing KV-cache
    when: Computes attention using cached K,V for old positions, only bind new token
    then: Returns output HV with O(1) new computation per cached position

  - name: decodeGreedy
    given: Output hypervector
    when: Finds nearest symbol in codebook via argmax cosine similarity
    then: Returns token string and confidence score

  - name: decodePhiRank
    given: Output hypervector, temperature, codebook
    when: Ranks all codebook entries by similarity, assigns phi^(-rank/T) weights, samples
    then: Returns sampled token with selection probability

  - name: decodeTopK
    given: Output hypervector, k, codebook
    when: Selects top-k most similar codebook entries, samples uniformly
    then: Returns sampled token from top-k set

  - name: decodeNucleus
    given: Output hypervector, p threshold, temperature, codebook
    when: Accumulates phi-rank weights until sum > p, samples from nucleus set
    then: Returns sampled token from nucleus

  - name: applyRepetitionPenalty
    given: Candidate similarities and recent_tokens list
    when: Divides similarity by penalty factor for tokens in recent window
    then: Returns adjusted similarities (penalized tokens less likely)

  - name: checkStopCondition
    given: Generated token and StreamState
    when: Checks EOS, max_length, min_confidence, repetition loop
    then: Returns whether to stop and reason string

  - name: generateStep
    given: Current StreamState
    when: Encode new token (or use cache), forward, decode, check stop
    then: Returns StreamToken and updated StreamState

  - name: generateStream
    given: Seed text and StreamConfig
    when: Runs generateStep in loop, yields tokens via callback
    then: Returns StreamStats when finished

  - name: slideWindow
    given: Current context exceeding max context_length
    when: Evicts oldest tokens from context and KV-cache, shifts positions
    then: Context and cache trimmed to fit within window

  - name: getStreamStats
    given: Completed or in-progress StreamState
    when: Computes timing, memory, cache hit rate, avg confidence
    then: Returns StreamStats
